%N A389533 a(n) is the largest number m in base n such that the digits of the pair (m, 2*m) use every digit in base n exactly once; a(n) = 0 if no such number exists.
%C A389533 Pairs using leading 0s, for example (03,12) in base 4, are considered invalid.
